This recording was done when one of the adult eagles flew into the nest. The other adult was sitting nearby and started calling (that is the higher pitched sound).  The nearby adult then flew into the nest and you can hear the calling get loader.  The low pitched calling is coming from the first adult while in the nest.
Two chicks near fledging, calling from the nest. Equipment Notes: Decoded MS Stereo.
'Chup' calls and various other calls by at least one unseen Golden Eagle. There were two birds at least in the area, but I could see either of them.

What seem to be begging calls of a juvenile Golden Eagle that is flying behind an adult, repeatedly, near the rim of the Mesa overlooking the Arroyo El Réparo. The wind was awful, and I suppressed 0-1000Hz to delete most of it, possibly deleting some of the sound… Recorded using a Sony PCM-D50 with a Sennheiser ME67 with a K6 power module & foam windscreen.
